{
  "stem": "7437.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And that's where we ended up.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "The only difference was that this new ghetto had an enclosure, again, with a high, wooden fence and barbed wire only on three sides because the fourth side was neighboring the-- a river that separated our town from a village.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And so somehow, my mother and my sister and I ended up-- I mean, our assignment was in a little, tiny room in a house right on the river.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And my mother, in retrospect, when I think-- she was a very wonderful woman.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And somehow, she instilled hope both in my sister and me, in all our neighbors, too.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "Somehow she gave us strength.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "I don't know if she had that strength and conviction within her.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "But on the outside, she seemed very strong and very loving and very hopeful.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "And she would always talk to my sister and me about the time when we would all be together again and that the war wouldn't last long and Papa would come home.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "And how she could do it, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "As a matter of, of, of fact, when they took my father away, she turned gray overnight.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "But I never saw my mother crying, never.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "Anyway, we ended up in the new ghetto.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "And everything continued as before.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "There is one incident.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "My sister was going to work, and at that time, somehow she was lucky.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "And she was able to obtain a job knitting articles of clothing for the soldiers on the front, the German soldiers.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "And that was a very favorable job because they were sitting in a old warehouse and they were protected from the elements, you know, winter and wind and whatever.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "Well, one day she was ill.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "And she wasn't able to go to work.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
